	<p>
	Tracing mode is a simple skeletonization method in which you work on a single tree with connected nodes.
	</p>

	<p>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr><th align="left">Mouse Shortcut</th><th align="left">Action</th></tr>
		</thead>
		<tr><td><span class="sh"><img src=":/resources/cheatsheet/leftclick.png" alt="Left click"/> on node</span></td><td>Select node</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="sh">Shift + <img src=":/resources/cheatsheet/leftclick.png" alt="Left click"/> drag</span></td><td>Draw selection square</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="sh"><img src=":/resources/cheatsheet/rightclick.png" alt="Right click"/></span></td><td>Place node</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="sh"><img src=":/resources/cheatsheet/middleclick.png" alt="Middle click"/> drag on node</span></td><td>Move node</td></tr>
		<tr><td><span class="sh">Shift + <img src=":/resources/cheatsheet/middleclick.png" alt="Middle click"/> scroll</span></td><td>Change active nodeâ€™s size</td></tr>
